<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Non-replaced inline-block elements in normal flow with auto margins</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#inlineblock-width" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="The computed value of auto for margin left or right becomes a used value of 0." />
        <style type="text/css">
            div
            {
                display: inline-block;
                width: 100px;
                height: 100px;
                margin-left: auto;
                background-color: blue;
            }
            body
            {
                margin: 0;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div></div>
        <p>Test passes if the blue box is in the top left of the page with no space between it and the edges of the browser.</p>
    </body>
</html>